Chocoalte Sheet Cake
  --America's Test Kitchen

Cake:
1 1/2 c sugar
1 1/4 c ap flour
1/2 tsp salt
1/2 tsp baking soda
1 c milk
8 oz bittersweet chocolate, chopped fine
3/4 c dutch process cocoa powder
2/3 c vegetable oil
4 eggs
1 tsp vanilla

Preheat oven to 325F; grease a 9x13" pan. Whisk sugar, flour, salt, and baking soda in a medium bowl. In a saucepan over low heat, add milk, chocolate, and cocoa powder; stir to combine. Once chocolate is melted and mixture is homogenous, take off heat and cool for 5 min. Whisk in oil, eggs, and vanilla until combined. Add dry ingredients into pot with chocolate mixture and whisk until completely combined. Pour into prepared pan and bake for 30-35 min, rotating halfway through. Cake is done when touching center it bounces back.

Frosting:
1 lb milk chocolate chopped 
2/3 c heavy cream
16 tbsp butter, room temp

Melt chocolate over double boiler with cream, 10-15 min. Whisk occasionally until thoroughly melted. Add butter and whisk in, let stand for 5 min. Put frosting in fridge for 30-60 min.

Let cake cool for 1-2 hrs before frosting.
